# .env Configuration Template

## Backend Environment (.env in shakti_alert/)

```env
# ===== FRONTEND AUTO-START (Development Only) =====
# Set to 'true' to auto-start frontend when running app.py locally
# For Railway deployment: set to 'false' or leave unset
SHAKTI_AUTO_START_FRONTEND=false

# ===== SERVER CONFIGURATION =====
# Port for Flask server (Railway sets this automatically)
PORT=5000

# Enable debugging (set to false in production)
DEBUG=false

# ===== EMAIL CONFIGURATION =====
gmail_user=your-email@gmail.com
gmail_app_password=your-app-password

# ===== API KEYS =====
gemini_api_key=your-gemini-key

# ===== WHATSAPP CONFIGURATION =====
waba_id=865491459160781
phone_number_id=867161659810934
whatsapp_permanent_token=your-token-here

# ===== PYTHON SETTINGS =====
# Important for Railway deployment
PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1
PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE=1
```

## Frontend Environment (.env in frontend/)

```env
# ===== API CONFIGURATION =====

# Development (local)
VITE_API_BASE=http://127.0.0.1:5000

# Production (Railway)
# VITE_API_BASE=https://your-backend-url.railway.app

# ===== BUILD CONFIGURATION =====
NODE_ENV=production
```

---

## How to Use These .env Files

### Local Development
1. Create `.env` file in `shakti_alert/` with above backend settings
2. Create `.env` file in `frontend/` with above frontend settings
3. Run: `python start_dev_windows.bat` (or `start_dev_linux.sh` on macOS/Linux)

### Railway Deployment

#### Backend Service
Add these to Railway environment variables:
- `SHAKTI_AUTO_START_FRONTEND=false`
- `gmail_user=...`
- `gmail_app_password=...`
- All other backend variables

#### Frontend Service
Add these to Railway environment variables:
- `VITE_API_BASE=https://your-backend-url.railway.app`
- `NODE_ENV=production`

---

## Security Notes

⚠️ **IMPORTANT**: Never commit `.env` files to Git!

1. Add `.env` to `.gitignore`:
   ```
   .env
   .env.local
   *.env
   ```

2. Use `.env.example` for documentation:
   - Commit `.env.example` with placeholder values
   - Never commit actual secrets

3. For Railway:
   - Use Railway's secret manager
   - Never paste secrets in code comments
   - Rotate API keys periodically

---

## Environment Variable Reference

| Variable | Purpose | Example |
|----------|---------|---------|
| `SHAKTI_AUTO_START_FRONTEND` | Auto-start frontend in dev | `false` |
| `PORT` | Server port | `5000` |
| `VITE_API_BASE` | Frontend API endpoint | `http://localhost:5000` |
| `gmail_user` | Gmail sender account | `email@gmail.com` |
| `gmail_app_password` | Gmail app password | `xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx` |
| `gemini_api_key` | Google Gemini API key | `AIzaXXX...` |

---

## Troubleshooting

### Environment variables not being loaded
- Windows: Make sure you're setting variables correctly (`set VAR=value`)
- Linux/Mac: Use `export VAR=value`
- Or use a `.env` file and ensure `load_dotenv()` is called in your Python code

### Frontend can't reach backend
- Check `VITE_API_BASE` is correct
- Make sure backend is running on specified port
- Check CORS headers in browser console

### Railway deployment fails
- Check all required environment variables are set
- Verify API keys are valid
- Check Python version compatibility

